Program: Omnibus
Title: The Bonus Army March
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mch
Last Broadcast Date: 14 February 2002
A quarter of the population was unemployed during the 1930s Depression in USA. A look at the 20,000 strong Bonus Army March, led by Walter W. Waters, a group of Army veterans who marched on Washington.